Straw packaging used at the Ferme des Trente Arpents

									11 July 2015 / 
									Products								
Cheeses from the Ferme des Trente Arpents are presented on straw mats. In addition to being visually pleasing and full of rustic charm, they are also a regional product.
+










 



Cheese: Truffled Brie with Alba White Truffle

									10 June 2015 / 
									Products								
To celebrate the end-of-year holidays, the Ferme des Trente Arpents is offering customers a new selection: Truffled Brie with Alba White Truffle.
+










 



Truffled Brie (Délice de Favières)

									4 May 2015 / 
									Products								
The holidays are an opportunity to indulge in prestigious regional products that are both authentic and original. In this spirit, as it does each year, the Ferme des Trente Arpents is selling one of its specialities: Brie stuffed with truffles.
+










 



Will there be a Brie de Coulommiers appellation?

									28 April 2015 / 
									Products								
Located in the town of Favières in Seine-and-Marne, the Ferme des Trente Arpents also lies in an area called ‘Brie Boisée’ which is the birthplace of the cheeses of the same name.
+










 



Honey and pollination

									6 February 2015 / 
									Products								
Since 2014, the Domaine des Trente Arpents has been developing a new business line: honey production. By establishing its first hives and hosting the hives of the region’s beekeepers, the estate is facilitating the natural pollination of surrounding farmlands.
+










 



Japan: the newest export market for the Ferme des Trente Arpents

									6 January 2015 / 
									Products								
Beginning in 2015, products from the Ferme des Trente Arpents will be exported to Japan.
+










 



Prepare for the Christmas holidays

									14 December 2014 / 
									Products								
Christmas and the New Year are always opportunities to sit down to an excellent meal, provided you know how to prepare your products.
+










 



How we make our Brie with Mustard

									17 November 2014 / 
									Products								
The delicate process of making our Brie with Mustard essentially uses three products: Farmstead Brie de Meaux, Délice de Jeannette and old-fashioned Meaux mustard.
+










 



Pommery Old-Fashioned Mustard: the other symbolic product of Meaux

									5 May 2014 / 
									Products								
Along with Brie cheese, mustard is one of the other great regional products made in Meaux. This ancient mustard-making tradition reached its peak in the 18th century, with the construction of several plants in Meaux.
+










 



Our first batch of honey

									10 April 2014 / 
									Products								
The farm’s honey production is becoming an increasingly important activity at the Domaine des Trente Arpents. The honey-making process fits with our efforts to promote sustainable farming and environmental awareness.
+






